                Before you Start configuring SQUID 
		do these following things to make an
		already difficult life a bit easier 
		====================================


1. Append the foll file - "squid_bash_profile"- to your /root/.bash_profile 
   and refresh it

   # cat squid_bash_profile >> /root/.bash_profile
   # . /root/.bash_profile

   The "squid_bash_profile"  contains :

   alias sq='squid -k reconfigure;[ $? = 0 ] && echo OK || echo Uh-OH'
   alias tailsquidaccess="tail -3f /var/log/squid/access.log"
   alias tailsquidcache="tail -3f /var/log/squid/cache.log"
   alias tailsquidstore="tail -3f /var/log/squid/store.log"

   Why ?

   # sq              will refresh squid everytime you change the config file
   # tailsquidaccess will show the access.log's last 3 lines in Real Time
   # tailsquidcache  will show the cache.log's last 3 lines in Real Time
   # tailsquidstore  will show the store.log's last 3 lines in Real Time

2. Copy the following files 

   porn
   noporn
   sa-blacklist.current.domains

   from the 4th CD in the workingconfigs/squid/ dir
   to /usr/local/squid/etc/ after, of course, creating the dir :

   # mkdir -p /usr/local/squid/etc/
   # cp -f /mnt/cdrom/workingconfigs/squid/porn /usr/local/squid/etc/
   # cp -f /mnt/cdrom/workingconfigs/squid/noporn /usr/local/squid/etc/
   # cp -f /mnt/cdrom/workingconfigs/squid/sa-blacklist.current.domains 
       /usr/local/squid/etc/

3. Copy the following file to /etc/pam.d/ :

   # cp squid-pam  /etc/pam.d/squid

4. Finally, the most important of ALL :
   
     Backup the canned squid.conf :
   
   # mv /etc/squid/squid.conf /etc/squid/squid.conf.redhat

     Replace it with our customized squid.conf.final :
     
   # cp squid.vadapav.final /etc/squid/squid.conf

     This is the file we will work with henceforth !

                         ******************
			 
   
